cz.syntea.xdef

Class XDFactory

  • java.lang.Object
    • cz.syntea.xdef.XDFactory

  • public final class XDFactory
extends java.lang.Object
    Provides generation of XDPool from source X-definitions. You can modify properties of compilation by parameters from properties (see XDConstants). In most of cases you can get XDPool directly by using of static methods of XDFactory class. You can also create a XDBuilder when you have to compile XDPool from different sources of X-definitions.

    The external methods must be static methods with compliant parameters to X-definition technology. The list of external classes with external methods can be passed as a parameter containing array of classes. If relevant method is not found in the list of classes then the generator of XDPool is searching the the method in the system class path.

    Typical use of XDFactory: 
    
 // 1. Create XDPool from one source and no properties:
 File xdef = ...
 XDPool xd = XDFactory.compileXD(null, xdef);
  ...
 // 2. Create XDPool from more sources and with properties:
 File[] xdefs = ...
 Properties props = new Properties();
 props.setProperty(key, value); //see XDConstants
 XDPool xd = XDFactory.compileXD(props, xdefs);
 ...

      • genXDPoolClass

        public static void genXDPoolClass(XDPool xp,
                                  java.lang.String dir,
                                  java.lang.String className,
                                  java.lang.String charset)
                           throws java.io.IOException
        Generate Java source class containing XDPool. You can get stored data if you invoke static method getXDPool() in generated class.
        Parameters:
        xp - XDPool object where is the X-definition with model from which Java source will be generated.
        dir - path to directory where write the source code.
        className - class name (file name will be "className.java").
        charset - the character set name or null (if null then it is used the system character set name).
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - if an error occurs.
